values: [Thanatos comes to the screen formally, square in the middle and dressing the public like a news caster. His eyes are set on the camera point, and he is focused.] Good evening residents of Demeleier. I see there have been a number of new arrivals. My apologies for not yet greeting you in person. I am Thanatos Rakke, I maintain the list of residents. If at any given opportunity you have time to view this list please do so. I will need to add the details of all new residents as soon as possible. It is imperative, the list is badly in need of an update. According to the calender I am using to keep track of the list, we are now in year three of our time here at Demeleier. Those who have been here the longest I'm sure will help those who are finding themselves here for the first time. A headcount or rollcall would also be appreciated. State yourself here if you please.

[Thanatos appears on the screen. It is dark but his shirtless figure can be made out. He is a little mud stained, and the shorter strands of his hair have come loose from his tight braid. He is broadcasting from the inn cellar, where several floorboards have been removed and in the ground beneath the man has dug out an almost perfect square about a metre in diameter and half a metre deep. It seems like he has likely spent more time making the square perfect that he has digging the thing, but that's Thanatos for you, he likes things just so.] Lady Yenyoji, if you would be so kind, I require your assistance at the inn cellar as soon as possible. Bring your staff with you, it is time to use your power. To other residents, fishermen and hunters especially, I urge you to gather as much meat and fish as possible over the next few days. With the snow so heavy I foresee it will only get worse as the moth continues. We will need our food stores to be as plentiful as possible. The items will be stored in this square which will be kept at freezing temperatures with the help of Yenyoji. The cold will keep things fresh. Iron links will be placed to keep it safe from the fae, and I believe we will be in need of someone to keep accounts as to what we have, and how it is distributed throughout the winder months. 'Trash' has volunteered himself for this, are there any other candidates for the position or shall it be entrusted to him? [VIOLA // 80%] I would like to see you tonight, if possible. I have a gift for you.

As a notice to old and new residents alike, I have recorded for your use an audio version of the initial information regarding Demeleier. I apologise for the time this has taken, it will be available shortly.

[ZELDA and SCHNEIZEL // 90%]

Taking on board the idea of young 'Trash' I have made enquiries as to putting together an underground ice box for the preservation of food. There is a mage among us, Yenyoji, who has agreed to maintain said box with the use of ice manipulation magic. 

The only question now I believe is where to place said storage. My chief idea was to remove several floorboards from the inn cellar and dig out a small square in the ground beneath. It will be easier to guard our food stores if they are indoors.

Your thoughts?


[MHYRTA // 90%]

I am afraid my activities last night have left me wounded. I am finding it difficult to walk, would it be possible to request a house call?

As always the watch meeting was enlightening. The young man named Seth mentioned to me that there was one among us who could manipulate ice? This could prove most useful, would that person please step forward if possible so that we may discuss a potential use of their talents? On another note, Ahiru, may I request your assistance today on a personal matter? As always residents, if your details are not on the residents list, please inform me as soon as possible.

<font size=1>[Thanatos is speaking into the camera though his eyes are at first affixed on a long piece of parchment. When he looks up from it, it is with a level of authority and the same serious nature he always carries.]</font> 

Once again the residents list requires an update. I implore you, residents of Demeleier, if you are not on this list please provide your details. We must have a way of monitoring those who are present and missing as well as provide something for newcomers to recognise their fellows amongst the flock. Information is key to survival.

If you know of anyone here who is not on the list provide me with their name, origin and time of arrival if at all possible. 

<font size=1>[He sets the parchment down slowly]</font>

As for the recent unpleasantness... <font size=1>[There is a sizeable pause, Thanatos's hand moves to sheild his eyes and remains there[</font> I am ready to answer any questions, and face any distrust. If there is a mutual decision from residents that someone other than myself should be responsible for the residents list, be it said.
Viola, warrior of music, died today.

[Thanatos is standing with his back to the camera but it is clearly him in the frame, the same tall dark presence as ever before. The long rope braid hanging down his back is bloodstained and soaked with rain as are the robes he wears. In his hand, though only the keened eyed would spot it, is a clump of ashen-pink hair. There is silence for a while, only the rain to fill the dead air before he addresses the listeners. The real Thanatos will see it as well, but any response he attempts to make he will only send to himself. As such all comments will be answered by the shadow.] Evil. Morally bad or wrong; wicked: an evil tyrant. Causing ruin, injury, or pain. Characterized by or indicating future misfortune. Bad or blameworthy by report; infamous: an evil reputation. Characterized by anger or spite. The quality of being morally bad or wrong; wickedness. That which causes harm, misfortune, or destruction. An evil force, power, or personification. Something that is a cause or source of suffering, injury, or destruction: the social evils of poverty and injustice. [Slowly Thanatos turns to face the camera, and it jumps with static as he does so, the heavy rain seeping into the scar on his face] Thanatos, Memory Keeper of Death. What an evil man he is. What an evil man I am.

The events of the past few days have left me drained and distant. For that I apologise. Obviously we are all aware by now that there is an oncoming danger likely to strike at any time. I believe that now more than ever it should be mandatory to travel in pairs or if possible trios to prevent any 'single twig being snapped', as Mr Hewley so wisely phrased it. [Thanatos pauses. He's felt like something is not quite right within him since the other night, and that worries him. Something is missing from him and the concept of that is more than a little unsettling.] The shadows that have appeared are also dangerous, and difficult to combat without magic. Avoid them where ever possible.

There is something I neglected to mention in my previous transmission. Something of a more personal nature. <font size=1>[There is no hesitance in the man's voice at all, despite personal matters usually being his least favourite subject]</font>

Aaron Gawain, would you allow me to escort you to the harvest festival tomorrow? I am aware you will be busy preparing the feast for a large part of the day, but when your labours are over, your company would be welcome. If you have already made other arrangements, do not trouble yourself.

I am guilty once more of being incredibly lax with the residents list. I feel it is not antiquate enough as it is, and require more information. Any that could be provided on missing residents would be of help. Particularly if you do not see your name on this list your assistance is required. I am sure at least half of those residing here are missing from the list, and that the 'place of residence' field of information as it stands is not useful at all. I will be removing it.

The recent influx of newcomers is disturbing to say the least. Though the fortifications seem to be going well, I feel that we are loosing the ability to keep track of all who are here. I ask once again, if you are absent from the crude yet somewhat effective residents list then please, your details are appreciated. [Private to Schneizel] Your Highness, do you feel that it is still appropriate to put out the information we collaborated on some time ago? If so, I believe there is no time like the present. I am also considering compiling a bestiary of this place, many residents, yourself included have had dealings with strange creatures that would do well to be documented. What is your opinion?

I apologise for my silence, and my absence. My concept of time is not like most and I lost many days to study without noticing they had passed. [On the screen there is a tall man surrounded by parchment sheets and loose bound books. Apparently he has been writing a great deal, and lost track of time while doing so. There is candle light illuminating a great deal of water damage in the room. The floor is covered with wooden boards to stop the mud from spreading.] I am aware I have not updated the residents list for some time. Newcomers over the past month or so, if you would be so kind as to introduce yourselves I would be most obliged, namely if you name is not on this list. Has anyone heard from the Professor on the front of lack of light? Also Duibhin, how do you fare for magical energy?

[The video is being broadcast from within the small chapel. It is a lot tidier inside nowadays and Thanatos is stood near one of the windows, so as to be well lit. He has chosen the chapel because he feels safe there from the song drifting into his ears from the loch. The beautiful melody plagues far too many of his thoughts.] My apologies for being incredibly lax with the updating of records and the list of residents [Demeleier residents list]. It seems no matter where I turn, something foul is going on concerning the fae. They certainty know how to keep one on their toes. I require everyone to meet at the chapel, as soon as possible. I am there now and will be waiting for the remainder of the day to see you all in turn. It is in regards to this. A head count would also be useful, there is still no sign of Miss La Bouff after all, though you will all be glad to know that the Professor is alive and... I hesitate to say well, however he is with us. That will be all.

<font size=1>[The video transmission comes on to show an odd sight. There is a closed door behind him, and his hair is down rather than tied back, and hanging at an oddly tense angle. The dark haired man on the video feed is glaring harshly at the communicator]</font> This may seem petty to some, perhaps even laughable. However, <font size=1>[He turns the camera to his backside, where his hair, and robes are jammed tightly in the door which is conveniently missing a handle on the outside and jammed tightly shut]</font> I do not find this the least bit amusing.

Assistance would be appreciated.

ATTENTION all Demeleier residents, and all children who have found themselves here today. Please, please make your way to the temple for a headcount. It is important we make sure everyone is safe and discover who has become a child, and who has not --- !!! Miss La Bouff, please be careful with that. If you break it you will not be given another. (ooc; So Thanatos has taken BB La Bouff to the temple, along with he hopes, BB Duib if he can convince him to come along. BB North is also there, and BB Prof. So, he's got a small collection of kiddies. Please treat this post as a PLAYPEN for them!)

I am no keeper of life... However, I feel it bears recordning. 

Mid April, Demeleier Second Year. Darryn Miquiztli returned to the living over twenty four hours after death.
Mid April, Demeleier Second Year. Darryn Miquiztli died from poisoning.

I am most aggravated. Today I have been looking back through the network only to find traces of two people, possibly more, who were here but are not here now. Why has this not been recorded sooner? I will rectify this immediately. The first person to disappear from Demeleier was one who called himself 'Other Father.' He was here, briefly at the beginning, and was last heard of here by his own transmission. The second person to vanish is this man, one Jackie. After his one and only network post he was not seen again. If there are others, please add them to this record. the information may or may not be of use, but if these men vanished we need to know. If they died here... It needs to be documented. ~ Demeleier Residents List

There are signs of a struggle at the loch's edge. [The video shows some muddy lines, as if something was dragged out of the water and through the sand, and also footprints, one set heavier than the other, leading off away from the waters edge. The markings are there due to the arrival of these two, but of course, the other residents don't know that!] Is everyone all right and accounted for? I know thus far that Darryn, Professor Treacle, North, Nel, Trash and Aaron are well and safe. [Update] I believe the answer to this query has now been answered. There are two newcomers here in Demeleier. More on this when there is more information to be had. ~ Demeleier Residents List

Strange occurrence's aught to be documented. Ten days since my arrival, I will call it mid march for want of an actual date, a strange curse seems to have come about the place. To put the oddities into points. There are snakes everywhere, though they do not appear any more dangerous than ordinary grass snakes. Something has transformed every form of drinkable liquid into a strong whisky. (For those who do not know, whisky is an alcoholic beverage originating from the world known as Earth.) There are green plants known as clover or shamrock growing in abundance. There is a legend on earth that finding a four leaved shamrock will bring the person luck. The 'faeries' making themselves known are little men, dressed in green. They are quick, and do not seem to want anything, however, I have my suspicions about them. It is possible that these beings are Leprechaun's, thought in this place, I am unsure. They do however, fit the description of such a mythical being as the Leprechaun. If anyone has yet to add to the list of residents please do so. I would like a complete list.

Greetings to all those I have not yet spoken to, I am Thanatos, a new arrival to Demeleier. Since it appears there is no way to leave this place, and hence forth no choice but to get settled, I vouch for a little organisation to commence.

There should be a record of everyone who is here, and I will take it upon myself to compile such a record. 

Residents if you would be so kind as to tell me your names, where you are from, the length of time you have been here thus far and perhaps a mention of where you are staying in Demeleier, I would be most obliged.

I have also noted that there is a rather sizeable town hall here, that is not in any kind of use. I suggest all residents report there for a headcount at least once every week to assure everyone is safe and perhaps to discuss and share information.

Your thoughts?
